### The Fundamental Barrier
No finite closed-form formula for p(n) exists (strong mathematical consensus, though no impossibility proof). The Lucy DP evaluating pi(x) at computed points IS the mathematical formula — it's as close to a "formula" as the structure of primes allows. The remaining ~6-step bisection in a 70-integer interval is root-finding (like computing sqrt(2) via Newton), not brute force.
